    SecurityPage --> AuditLogs: Click Audit Logs Tab
    SecurityPage --> AccessMonitoring: Click Access Monitoring Tab
    SecurityPage --> DataBackup: Click Data Backup Tab
    SecurityPage --> SecurityPermissions: Click Security Permissions Tab
    
    AuditLogs --> LogEntryDetails: Click on Log Entry
    AuditLogs --> ExportLogsDialog: Click Export Logs
    
    AccessMonitoring --> LoginSessionDetails: Click on Login Session
    AccessMonitoring --> LockAccountDialog: Click Lock Account
    
    DataBackup --> BackupDetails: Click on Backup Entry
    DataBackup --> ManualBackupDialog: Click Manual Backup
    
    SecurityPermissions --> RoleDetails: Click on Role
    SecurityPermissions --> CreateRoleDialog: Click Create Role
    
    LogEntryDetails --> AuditLogs: Click Back
    LoginSessionDetails --> AccessMonitoring: Click Back
    BackupDetails --> DataBackup: Click Back
    RoleDetails --> SecurityPermissions: Click Back
    
    ExportLogsDialog --> AuditLogs: After Export/Cancel
    ManualBackupDialog --> DataBackup: After Start/Cancel
    LockAccountDialog --> AccessMonitoring: After Confirm/Cancel
    CreateRoleDialog --> SecurityPermissions: After Create/Cancel
    
    note right of AuditLogs
        Audit Logs provide a detailed record
        of all administrative actions for
        accountability and monitoring purposes.
        Logs can be filtered by date, user,
        action type, or module.
    end note
    
    note right of AccessMonitoring
        Access Monitoring tracks all login
        activity and identifies suspicious
        patterns such as unusual locations,
        multiple failed attempts, or off-hours
        access, enabling quick corrective action.
    end note
    
    note left of DataBackup
        Data Backup enables scheduled or
        manual backups of all platform data,
        with options for storage location,
        retention policy, and encryption to
        ensure data integrity and recovery.
    end note
    
    note left of SecurityPermissions
        Security Permissions manages role-based
        access control across the platform,
        allowing granular permission settings
        for different user roles and modules.
    end note
